div.p:
"Nay, nay, dear Kate," I replied, "we may be all the better for such visions;
                     for I have a strong suspicion that those who never dream, have never
                        truly lived."

"'Sir,' said she, 'I wish I was in Cuba. I had just such a humming-bird at home;
                  and I fed it with orange boughs full of white flowers, every day; but you have no
                  orange trees here, and I have no papa!'
